article_title: Proof of a ‘Gig Economy’ Revolution Is Hard to Find
article_text:
Politicians and Silicon Valley prospectuses are all atwitter over the perils and promise of the next big thing, the gig economy.

Hillary Clinton warned of the downsides of this informal workforce in a recent economic speech, including the potential erosion of workplace protections. Eyeing an opening, Jeb Bush used the ride-hailing app Uber to get to a meeting with Thumbtack, a company that helps people hire everyone from handymen to...

twitter.description: Politicians and Silicon Valley prospectuses are all atwitter over the perils and promise of the next big thing, the gig economy. But the numbers don’t bear that out: Americans are becoming slightly less likely to be self-employed, and less prone to hold multiple jobs.
twitter.creator: @JoshZumbrun
